Fantastic tacos, and I say this as someone from SoCal.  $2.50 each. I loved the lengua here, which was shredded, but had a nice melty fatty texture. I also really enjoyed the carnitas, which had a good mixture of textures with some bits with some crunch mixed in with the rest. The chorizo was full of flavor and had that tougher texture that I sometimes enjoy chewing on. The cabeza and pastor were alright, but I'd get the other 3 first.

I’ve ordered from these guys numerous times over the past couple years and the food is always great. I’ve recommended them to my boyfriend and friends when they’re around because the quality and prices can’t be beat. I’ve finally decided to leave a review just because I ordered from them yesterday and it wasn’t as good as it usually is. After waiting about an hour more or less for my food, I gave the delivery guy $20 for the six tacos I ordered, expecting to get back $9.50 (before tipping) since they’ve been $1.75 each for the longest time. You can imagine my surprise and confusion when he only gave me back $5. I pointed it out as a mistake and he said the tacos were $2.50 each, not $1.75. So I just said okay and left it at that, but it would’ve been nice to know beforehand that their menu prices have changed. I usually don’t even keep cash on me and decided last minute to withdraw a $20 instead of exact change, which was good thinking in hindsight, because it would’ve sucked if I was unknowingly short almost $5 and who knows what would’ve happened then. But regardless, the food was good as usual, however the packaging was pretty poor. The container the tacos came in was soggy and greasy on the outside, and the paper bag the container was in was equally as soggy as well, which is pretty gross but not a huge deal. I got 3 chicken and 3 pork tacos, and the chicken was pretty dry without adding the included sauces on the side to it and a little bit of the pork was chewy. I don’t know what happened on their end but overall the taste was still pretty close to as good as it usually is in the end.

This place is quite awesome! I came here with a friend around 3PM, and I got a bistec, a carnitas, and a pastor taco. The tacos all came with radish, cucumber, and onion too, and there was a green sauce and a spicy red sauce on the counter. The taco truck had a warm space to stand and eat too, which was pretty great. The steak was super flavorful and really delicious, and I loved the pastor too because there were chopped pineapple on top. The carnitas was a bit too fatty for me, and it was less flavorful than the other two meats. Definitely would recommend though! At $2 (including tax), you can't beat that price for tacos out of a truck! If I lived closer to here, I would be eating here often.
